💯…The strongest friendships I have are with women who TRULY empower, love, celebrate, and support their friends.  When you don’t feel empowered and you come from a place of jealousy, scarcity, and insecurity you can’t authentically uplift the women around you.  I’m grateful to be surrounded by women who are for me and that remind me daily what true friendships should feel like…I’m especially thankful that Kaia gets to see what this looks like so she can be a girl that celebrates other girls 💞💞. Too many to tag but if you’re reading this you know who you are…and feel free to tag a friend below or send this to someone who celebrates YOU.
Thank you God for 36 years 🙏🏽🎂 This year had a lot of highs & lows and it’s taught me what & who truly matters.  Grateful for the people I get to do life with who love me for me 🤎

2022 taught me that no matter what you’re going through in life it’s a lot easier with good friends by your side that make you laugh.  And thank you @supper.land for a delicious NYE dinner 🥘🥂🎆🤍
2023 energy- more gratitude…thanking God for the highs & lows…telling the people in your life you love them every chance you get…choosing JOY in all circumstances.

Eden Amelia Blount 🤍 April 26, 2021-May 4, 2023 

Eden Amelia Blount passed away peacefully on May 4, 2023 in her daddy’s arms with her big brothers and mother by her side. 

She fought with strength and courage until the very end and is now healed in heaven. 

While her life was short, every day was filled with so much love and the joy that Eden brought to this world is immeasurable.  She will be dearly missed by so many but we rejoice that her fight is over and she is now in the arms of our Heavenly Father.

She is survived by her loving parents, Gary and Stephanie, her brothers Noah, Luke, Levi, and Jude, Grandparents, Rick and Lori Cloninger, Grandfather, Gary Blount Sr. (Shelba) Grandmother, Deborah Thomas (Danny) , Uncles, Chris Cloninger, Ryan (Meredith) Cloninger, Marshall (Alaina) Blount, Aunt, Ryleigh Blount.

I love this first photo because it sums up exactly who you are as a father.  Your heart was forever changed the day you became a dad and from that moment on everything you’ve ever done has been with the mindset of building the best life for your daughters and for me.  Raising small children is hard and I thank God every single day that you are who I have as a partner (even the days I’m being Bratalie 🤪). When we took over @charlotte_lately (from @courtneyallybs) we had no idea what we were doing. What we did know was that we love Charlotte, it’s our home, it’s where we want to grow our family, and we are passionate about learning & sharing other people’s stories and the good things that are happening all around us.  We have some exciting things to come that we can’t wait to share and today I am grateful to work side by side with the one who always points me back to what my purpose is and is a constant reminder of God’s sovereignty and that ALL THINGS WORK TOGETHER FOR GOOD. 🖤

Kaia started Kindergarten last year but we ended up bringing her back to her preschool for a TK year.  So grateful for the time she got to make some beautiful friendships, how well she was loved by all of her teachers and how it built her confidence…and the sweetest part was that she got a year at the same school to be big sister to Nora and her cousin Elden.  Kaia is so empathetic and nurturing so it was a really special year for our family full of growth and lots of good memories. This morning she was ready to go and excited for her new school, teachers and friends…no nerves or hesitation until the sweetest little pause when she went to say goodbye and hug her sissy and told her she couldn’t wait to see her after school. 😢💞 

We have felt ALL the love and such a warm welcome into a new school and community and feel so blessed already by everyone’s kindness and support in this new season and chapter.  God’s timing is always better than our own 🙏🏽💙🤍 Praying for a healthy and wonderful year ahead for all of our kids and sending lots of love to everyone.

We are beyond excited to partner alongside @jonathanstewar1 to kickoff our “Glory Days Icons Collection” with the launch of his shirt.  We’re so grateful for the support Jonathan and his family have shown us over the years, and this entire community as a whole.  What makes this collaboration so rad isn’t only the opportunity to partner alongside him to make an iconic shirt celebrating his legacy, but to also do some great things in the community. Proceeds from the sale of Stew’s shirt will go to benefit his friend and former teammate’s @stevesmithfdn . 
•
J. Stew will also be doing a shirt signing at our store on Thursday, Sept. 28 from 4-6pm.  Grab your shirt now (in-store or online) or scoop one on the 28th and get it signed ✍️!
•
An additional fun fact - the artist responsible for this incredible design might take you back to your GLORY DAYS of the old caricature style sports tees.  We are privileged to work with our friend, @mudgestudios who created some of your childhood iconic tees of the 80’s and 90’s.  It’s a joy that we get to bring that same legendary look to some icons we admire today like J. Stew!

Make sure you follow along so you don’t miss it, stay tuned! 📺

Bahakel Entertainment is proud to announce the premiere date of “LATELY,” our newest reality series hosted by the incredible Natalie and Jonathan Stewart! 🎉📺

This season on #Lately, you’ll meet everyone from bakers with special needs, to a 100-year-old World War II veteran, and a woman who changed her entire company to save jobs for her employees, too! “We love to learn about different cities through their local food scene and have always enjoyed meeting new people and hearing their stories and connecting with them,” said  @nataliestewar1 

When @jonathanstewar1 made it big with the @panthers, he always knew he wanted to give back to the Queen City, saying” “We’ve always been passionate about local businesses and truly believe they are the heartbeat of our community.” 

And that’s exactly what “Lately” does… illuminates impactful stories from right here in the Queen City. The show premieres Saturday, November 25th at 7pm on @wccbcharlotte and streams on the WCCB app. Prepare to be inspired! 

*Available on Roku, Apple TV and Amazon Fire TV Stick. You can also download the app for your phone or tablet in the App Store or Google Play Store. Or watch online at bahakelentertainment.com

Dressember is a global movement utilizing fashion and creativity to combat human trafficking and protect people in poverty from violence. This year #Dressember partnered with IJM (@ijm) to resource prevention, advocacy, intervention, and survivor empowerment programs to continue the fight against human trafficking.

I will be joining thousands of advocates around the world by wearing a dress every day in December to raise awareness and funds to fight human trafficking.

There are a few ways you can get involved in this year’s campaign. Join my team and participate in this challenge with me. If you don’t want to participate the whole month, Dressember For a Day is TOMORROW. Join my team, wear a dress, and fundraise for the day! (link in my bio) 👗🤍 #dressember2023

This year I really fell in love with film because it’s kind a metaphor for where I am in life right now.  It might not be the “perfect” photo because, unlike a digital camera/iPhone, you don’t take 20 of them and scroll through to pick out the best one with everyone smiling and every hair perfectly in place.  It captures you exactly as you are and I think they are beautiful in the imperfections and they remind us to spend less time worrying about all of the “filters”we use, literally and figuratively, to try and make things appear better than they are.  Perfection isn’t my goal in this season of life…living a life with purpose and more gratitude & loving my people well/loving myself well is my goal.

It makes me think a lot about all of the posts I’ve seen lately reminding us that Instagram is a highlight reel.  We all have our own struggles and battles we’re fighting so if this year was hard for you just know that you’re not alone.  2023 was full of a lot of highs but also some of my lowest of lows. It’s taught me a lot about what matters, who matters, what deserves time and a response and what definitely doesn’t, it’s shown me areas where I can grow, I learned that navigating life’s ups and downs often requires us to toggle between feelings of joy and grief— you can feel sorrow and joy simultaneously along with a multitude of other feelings…and most importantly this year has shown me that God will always carry me through the hard times and his 𝓰𝓇𝒶𝒸ℯ 𝒾𝓈 𝓈𝓊𝒻𝒻𝒾𝒸𝒾ℯ𝓃𝓉. 

@jonathanstewar1 I’m grateful for our perfectly imperfect life and these precious girls of ours 🙏🏽❤️🤍
